According to the State Perkins plan, the State will focus on CTE programs of study in the Health and Bioscience, Information Technology, and Manufacturing, Engineering and Technology career clusters. With over 11,000 students enrolled, the CTE Engineering program has one of the highest participation rates. Information Technology (IT) is listed as a high-skill, high-wage, and in-demand occupation field provided through CTE.; 
