The State’s Governor also started the Massachusetts Workforce Skills Cabinet through an executive order. The cabinet is comprised of the Secretaries of Labor, Education and Economic Development. They use “labor market analysis to drive investment of $85.6 million in annual State funding to build new supply “pipelines” for individuals aligned with regional priority industries and occupations based on business demand.” One of its most recent initiatives has been providing Skills Capital Grants to schools. These grants help schools upgrade their technology and provide programs in various fields, including engineering.; 
