Network2Work @PVCC creates a pathway that will provide individuals with the resources he or she needs to secure the job they identify as a good match. Resources may include (1) Work skills (e.g., literacy, workplace readiness, or technical), (2) Life management (e.g., childcare, transportation, stable shelter, or apparel) or (3) Health (e.g., physical, mental, or substance abuse recovery). ;
The New Economy Workforce Credential Grant Program was developed during the 2016 General Assembly Session to create and sustain a supply of credentialed workers to fill high-demand occupations in fields which support the State’s economy while making the attainment of these credentials more affordable. This grant program provides a pay-for-performance model for funding noncredit workforce training that leads to a credential in a high demand field.;
